<TITLE> BSF kills Bangladeshi at Panchagarh border </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Panchagarh, Feb (bdnews24.com)  India's Border Security Force reportedly killed a Bangladeshi and took the body into India near the Haribhasha border in Panchagarh district on Wednesday. The dead Bangladeshi was identified by locals as Islam Mia, 38, son of late Afisuddin of Madhupara village in Sadar upazila. Bangladesh Rifles (BDR) officials said the incident took place at around 2.30pm. Panchagarh 25th Rifles Battalion official Hasibul Hossain said Islam was working in a field near Sub-pillar No 25 and 26 of the Main Pillar No 748. "Suddenly, some BSF 48th Battalion personnel, based at the Singimari post, fired at Islam. He was dead on the spot. Later BSF personnel took his body into the Indian Territory," he said. He also said that BDR had sent a protest note to the BSF regarding this issue and also called for a flag meeting between the two border forces. bdne
